"Here is a Python coding problem for you, along with the answer and tests in JSON format as requested:\n\n```json\n{\n    \"title\": \"Number Reverser (Easy)\",\n    \"description\": \"Write a function `reverse_number` that takes an integer as input and returns its reverse. For example, if the input is 12345, the output should be 54321.\\n\\n#### Function Signature:\\n```python\\ndef reverse_number(num: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input:\\n- `num` (int): An integer to be reversed.\\n\\n#### Output:\\n- Returns the reversed integer.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"def reverse_number(num: int) -> int:\\n    reversed_num = 0\\n    while num > 0:\\n        digit = num % 10\\n        reversed_num = reversed_num * 10 + digit\\n        num //= 10\\n    return reversed_num\\n\",\n    \"tests\": [\n        \"assert reverse_number(12345) == 54321\",\n        \"assert reverse_number(12000) == 21\",\n        \"assert reverse_number(1000) == 1\",\n        \"assert reverse_number(153463) == 346351\"\n    ]\n}\n```"